EXIT_FEE is now a protocol level fee.  (#149)

* Added tests for extreme weights (BONE and 49BONE). Improved current tests with for example pAi = exitswap_ExternAmountOut(exitswap_PoolAmountIn(pAi))

* Forgot to add new test file in last commit

* Added EXIT_FEE as a protocol level fee that goes to BLabs. Removed the possibility of setting exitFee for pool. Corrected related functions

* Created EXIT_FEE constant, this is the protocol level fee charged. Pool controllers can no longer add an exit fee for the pool. The exit fee is now charged also when liquidity is withdrawn from controlled pools. Most tests passing.

* Added require that does not allow the price after the trade to be lower than before the trade, this would mean a math bug has been exploited. Any trade can only be executed if the effective price is worse than the initial spotPrice

* Added require that makes sure that the effective price paid (Ai/Ao) is higher than spotPrice before trade. If not, a math bug happened.

* Update contracts/BPool.sol

* Replaced all setFee / getFee by setSwapFee / getSwapFee

* fix failing tests on BPool after changing <= on MAX WEIGHT
